Such passages as Verg. Aen. 11. 282, ‘Quibus Hector ab oris Expectate venis?' (and add x. 811, ΧΠ. 947, Pers. 111. 29) are not parallel, as the vocative does not contain the main predication.

Tibur, twenty miles from Rome, was a fashionable locality at this time, much more esteemed than the neighbouring Sabine district, and praised by Horace, Od. 1. vii. 13, 1. xviii. 2, 11. vi. 5, 1v. iii. 10. There the great, such as Maecenas, Sallust, Quintilius Varus, had their villas ; and Catullus eon· sesses his desire for the vanity of a fashionable address.
